response.question: Q5: What is the time complexity of linear search?
response.correct_answer: The time complexity of linear search is O(n) for the worst-case and average-case scenarios.
response.feedback: The student's answer is correct. This question was not found in the provided reference material and was evaluated based on standard academic knowledge. The worst-case and average-case time complexity for a linear search is O(n), as the algorithm may have to examine every element in a list of size n. The student provided the correct Big O notation.
